# SQL Data Warehouse Project Report

## 1. Project Overview

This project demonstrates the design and implementation of a modern SQL Data Warehouse using PostgreSQL. The objective was to transform raw business data from multiple source systems into a structured analytical model that supports business intelligence and reporting.

The solution follows the Medallion Architecture approach consisting of Bronze, Silver, and Gold layers. Data is extracted from CRM and ERP source systems, cleansed and standardized in the Silver layer, and transformed into business-ready dimensions and fact tables in the Gold layer.

---

## 2. Business Problem

Organizations often receive data from multiple systems that contain inconsistencies, duplicate records, missing values, and varying formats. Such issues make reporting unreliable and hinder decision-making.

The objective of this project is to:

* Consolidate data from multiple source systems.
* Improve data quality through validation and cleansing.
* Create a scalable data warehouse architecture.
* Provide a trusted source of data for analytics and reporting.

